cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS

This paper proposes a new modelling language and automated reasoning functionalities for goal models, which are commonly used in software engineering. The use of automated reasoning technologies such as satisfiability and optimization modulo theories suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also addresses limitations in existing techniques for coping with complex real-world problems, indicating a potential fit with software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the experimental evaluation suggests a potential fit with data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) for scalability testing.
